Title: Twisted K-theory and K-theory of bundle gerbes

Authors: P. Bouwknegt (1), A. L. Carey (1), V. Mathai (1 and 2), M. K. Murray

(1) and D. Stevenson (1) ((1) University of Adelaide, (2) MIT)Comments: 29 pages, corrected typos, added references, included new section on

twisted Chern character in non-torsion caseJournal-ref: Commun.Math.Phys. 228 (2002) 17-49

In this note we introduce the notion of bundle gerbe K-theory and investigatethe relation to twisted K-theory. We provide some examples. Possibleapplications of bundle gerbe K-theory to the classification of D-brane chargesin non-trivial backgrounds are discussed.